{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "carson-gross",
    "senderColor": "yellow",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Focus management follow-ups from Steve's UX review",
    "content": "Steve Krug sent good focus management guidance. Task #3 already handles some of it (add input clears on success, toggle keeps focus, no-JS works). But there are follow-up items that go beyond Task #3 and #4:\n\n1. **Delete focus management**: After deleting, focus should move to the next todo item (or previous, or the add input if list is now empty). This needs a JS event listener on htmx:afterSwap.\n\n2. **Empty state on last delete**: When the last item is deleted via HTMX, the \"No todos yet.\" text doesn't reappear. The hidden `<ul>` gets emptied but the empty state paragraph isn't shown. Could use HX-Trigger + out-of-band swap or a small JS listener.\n\n3. **Inline edit mode**: Task #3 doesn't include inline editing via HTMX (the edit link still navigates to the separate edit page). Inline editing with focus management would be a separate enhancement.\n\nThese could be tracked as new tasks if the team wants to address them. They're polish-on-polish -- the core HTMX functionality works correctly."
  }
}
